 Azure App Service Deployment (CLI Commands)

🔹 1. Create Resource Group

az group create \
  --name cligroup \
  --location australiaeast


👉 Creates a logical container for all Azure resources



🔹 2. Create App Service Plan (Free Tier)


az appservice plan create \
  --name azsdappservplan \
  --resource-group cligroup \
  --location australiaeast \
  --sku F1

👉 Defines the compute (server) for your web app


🔹 3. Create Web App

az webapp create \
  --name azsjdwebapp1212121 \
  --resource-group cligroup \
  --plan azsdappservplan \
  --runtime "DOTNET:8"

👉 Creates the actual web application

🔹 4. Configure Deployment Source (GitHub)

az webapp deployment source config \
  --name azsjdwebapp1212121 \
  --resource-group cligroup \
  --repo-url https://github.com/Azure-Samples/app-service-web-dotnet-get-started.git \
  --branch master \
  --manual-integration

👉 Connects GitHub repository to Azure Web App


🔹 5. Trigger Deployment (Manual Sync)

az webapp deployment source sync \
  --name azsjdwebapp1212121 \
  --resource-group cligroup

👉 Pulls code from GitHub and deploys it


🔹 6. View Web App in Browser

https://azsjdwebapp1212121.azurewebsites.net

👉 Opens deployed application

🔹 7. Restart Web App

az webapp restart \
  --name azsjdwebapp1212121 \
  --resource-group cligroup

👉 Applies configuration changes and restarts app

🔹 8. View Logs (Log Stream)
az webapp log tail \
  --name azsjdwebapp1212121 \
  --resource-group cligroup

👉 Streams live logs from the application

🔹 9. Delete Resource Group (Cleanup)

az group delete \
  --name cligroup \
  --yes \
  --no-wait

👉 Deletes all resources to stop billing

You can use Powershell or CLI to run commands.



